    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - CHASSIS ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Allison
        Automatic Transmission System With T-444E, DT-466E, I-530E
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Allison Automatic Transmission System With T-444E, DT-466E, I-530E</title>
        <table id="t0823902" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Allison Automatic Transmission System With T-444E, DT-466E, I-530E</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.57in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.63in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.79in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.31in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Will engine crank over when the trans. is in neutral and the key sw. (24) is moved to
                                the start position?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F17 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F17</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then correct. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At F17, measure voltage from circuit 13B to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F17, 13B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 13B, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With key off, disconnect engine harness dash conn. (2A) from cab dash conn. (2). Turn
                                key on and at conn. (2), measure voltage from circuit 97P to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(2), 97P to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage, in circuit 97P, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Install jumper wire to circuit 97P between conn. (2) and (2A). At (2A), with trans. in
                                neutral and key switch on, measure voltage from circuit 97AU to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(2A), 97AU to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect neutral position switch (438) and measure voltage from circuit 97P to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(438), 97P to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 97P, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With trans. in neutral position, measure resistance of neutral position switch
                                (438).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(438), across term.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 97AU, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace neutral position switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (2A) and remove crank inhibit relay (661). Turn key sw. (24) to
                                ignition position and at (661) circuit 97L, measure voltage to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(661), 97L to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 97AU, conn. (386), or circuit 97L, then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Refer to Starting Motor System Circuits and Components section for further trouble-
                                shooting.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F1 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>F1</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then correct. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At fuse F1 and circuit 13, measure voltage to ground</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F1, 13 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 13, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove modulator solenoid relay from socket (403). Turn key sw. on and measure voltage
                                from circuit 92E and then 92B to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(403), 92E and 92B to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts each location.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 92E/92D or 92B/92D, circuit 92D, relay
                                conn. (402) or dash conn. (2), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At socket (403), measure voltage from circuit 92B to 92C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(403), 92B to 92C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 16.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Bench test modulator sol. relay by verifying that contacts at pin 30 and 87 are closed
                                when de-energized and open when relay is energized. Does relay test good?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With key off, disconnect ECM conn. (379) and install a jumper from circuit 92F to gnd.
                                At (403) measure resistance from circuit 92F to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(403), 92F to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Remove jumper and refer to Engine Diag- nostic Manual.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 92F, conn. (402), or circuit 92F, then
                                repair. Remove jumper and reconnect connectors.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install modulator solenoid relay (403) and disconnect modulator shift solenoid
                                conn. (404). Turn key on and measure voltage from circuit 92C to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(404), 92C to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 92C or conn. (389), then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (404) measure voltage from circuit 92C to 92-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(404), 92C to 92-G.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 92-G, conn. (389), or circuit 92-G/11-GJ,
                                then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect modulator sol. at (404) and listen for it to shift. Did it click? Reconnect
                                ECM conn. (379).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Allison automatic trans. circuits check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace modulator solenoid.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
